name: NYDailyNews
text:
The Jamal Adams trade will make or break Jets GM Joe Douglas.

Douglas shipped one of the NFL’s biggest stars to Seattle on Saturday for a boatload of draft capital that he hopes will set a new foundation for the star-crossed franchise.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
The Nets won a scrimmage with the Spurs 124-119, showing progress in Orlando.

The Nets shot 43% from the field as a team, and a bright spot, once again, was Rodions Kurucs, who came off the bench at the center position and shot 3-of-3 from downtown.
https://t.co/940TPp283G

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Florida surpassed New York with 414,511 total coronavirus cases, racing past New York’s 411,200.

The new case total puts Florida at second-highest total in the nation. California currently has more than 440,000.
https://t.co/dDgdGQONdZ

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Playboy cover girl Bo Black, the wife of Brewers manager Tom Trebelhorn, is dead at 74.

Black, who was adored in her adopted city of Milwaukee for presiding over the annual Summerfest celebration, died in Arizona after a lengthy health decline.
https://t.co/zRBra8pV18

text:
Is the NYC Board of Elections ready for November’s presidential election?

text:
A 37-year-old man was fatally shot in the Bronx early Sunday around 3 a.m., cops said.

The victim was blasted in the head outside a building on Bronx Park East near Britton St. in Allerton.  The NYPD had no immediate arrests.

text:
An NYPD SUV racing to the scene of a Brooklyn shooting fatally struck a motorcyclist, cops said Sunday.

The marked NYPD Ford Explorer was on Metropolitan Ave. in Williamsburg with its lights and sirens on when it slammed into a 37-year-old motorcyclist.

text:
HEARTLESS
Two crooks tried to rob a disabled Bronx man, 35, by pulling his wheelchair out from under him — & kicking him in the face.

The victim, lying helpless on the floor, was patted down by the robbers.

NYPD released video and need the public's help.
